&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT NOOKS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nooks is pioneering Classified-Infrastructure-as-a-Service (CIaaS) — designing, building, and operating Sensitive Compartmented Information Facilities (SCIFs) and other secured, classified environments for the defense and national security community. We work with the agencies, contractors, and mission-driven organizations that keep the nation safe, delivering the physical infrastructure that makes classified work possible. We’re growing fast, operating across multiple markets, and building a company that takes both the mission and the business seriously.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Information Security (INFOSEC) IT Generalist to support the U.S. Space Force’s Sensitive Compartmented Information (SCI) and Intelligence, Surveillance, and Reconnaissance (ISR) network as part of our Integrated Security Enterprise (ISE) program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role helps to ensure that all IT operations comply with the physical, technical, and personnel security standards mandated by DoDM 5105.21-V1 and related Intelligence Community Directives (ICDs).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Systems Compliance:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain security controls for SCI systems in accordance with DoDM 5105.21 and ICD 503/RMF standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Incident Response:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the identification, reporting, and mitigation of security violations or &quot;spillages&quot; (Data Transfers) between classification levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; SCIF Operations:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and manage IT infrastructure within Sensitive Compartmented Information Facilities (SCIFs), ensuring TEMPEST integrity and physical security of hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Access Management:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer Identity and Access Management (IdAM) for SCI-level networks, ensuring the principle of &quot;need-to-know&quot; is strictly enforced.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Audit &amp;amp; Continuous Monitoring:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct weekly system audits, vulnerability scans, and continuous monitoring to maintain the Authorization to Operate (ATO).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Policy Development:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft and update System Security Plans (SSP) and Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for SCI-cleared personnel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE SKILLSET:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: 1-3 years in IT security, with at least 1 year specifically managing SCI or SAP-level systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Depth: Must meet DoD 8140/8570.01-M requirements (typically IAT Level II or III, e.g., Security+, or CISM).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge: In-depth understanding of DoDM 5105.21-V1, ICD 705 (SCIF construction), and NIST SP 800-53.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearance: Must possess and maintain either an Interim Secret or Secret eligibility security clearance. U.S. Citizenship is required. Candidates must be capable of maintaining eligibility up to the Secret level within 45 days of hire.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This position supports mission operations and may require occasional travel to government facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT NOOKS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nooks is pioneering Classified-Infrastructure-as-a-Service (CIaaS) — designing, building, and operating Sensitive Compartmented Information Facilities (SCIFs) and other secured, classified environments for the defense and national security community. We work with the agencies, contractors, and mission-driven organizations that keep the nation safe, delivering the physical infrastructure that makes classified work possible. We’re growing fast, operating across multiple markets, and building a company that takes both the mission and the business seriously.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Physical Security Generalist to support the US Space Force classified enterprise. This is a hands-on role focused on the execution and sustainment of physical security requirements for Sensitive Compartmented Information Facilities (SCIFs) and other classified spaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Physical Security Generalist will work under the direction of the SSO and senior security leadership to support SCIF operations, inspections, documentation, and compliance activities. This role emphasizes implementation, coordination, and continuous compliance, rather than program ownership or final approval authority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. SCIF Operations &amp;amp; Compliance Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the day-to-day physical security operations of accredited SCIFs in accordance with ICD 705 and applicable DoDMs/AFMANs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with SCIF accreditation, re-accreditation, and change management activities by preparing documentation and tracking compliance actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records related to SCIF accreditations, inspections, waivers, and security incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Physical Security Systems &amp;amp; Access Control&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and monitor physical access control systems (PACS), including badging, card readers, and access logs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support alarm system testing, maintenance coordination, and response procedures in coordination with monitoring services and on-site personnel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforce visitor control procedures, including verification of access approvals, visitor badging, and escort requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Construction Security &amp;amp; Facility Changes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support construction security activities for new SCIF builds or modifications to existing facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the review of construction plans, drawings, and change requests to ensure alignment with physical security requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with facilities, construction, and IT teams to ensure maintenance and upgrades are executed in compliance with ICD 705.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4. Risk Management &amp;amp; Incident Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with physical security risk assessments and vulnerability analyses for classified spaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the documentation and reporting of physical security incidents or anomalies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track corrective actions and mitigation measures to closure under the guidance of senior security leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;5. Training, Audits &amp;amp; Coordination&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support physical security awareness and facility access training efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with internal self-inspections and external compliance audits (e.g., DCSA or customer-led inspections).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
